# Detox E2E (Testing Agents)

## Config and Specs

- **Config:** `.detoxrc.js` (apps, devices, configurations).
- **E2E Jest:** `e2e/jest.config.js`.
- **Specs:** `e2e/**/*.e2e.js` (e.g. `e2e/landing.e2e.js`).

## Commands (for Fixing Agent / test-and-fix)

- **iOS:** `npm run e2e:ios` or `detox test -c ios.sim.debug`
- **Android (emulator):** `npm run e2e:android` or `detox test -c android.emu.debug`
- **Android (attached device):** `npm run e2e:android:attached` or `detox test -c android.att.debug`
- **Build first if needed:** `npm run e2e:build:ios` / `npm run e2e:build:android` / `npm run e2e:build:android:attached`

Use **testing target** from user (iOS Simulator / Android Emulator) to choose the command.

## Native setup (must exist before running)

- **Android:** `DetoxTest.java` in `android/app/src/androidTest/.../<applicationId>/`; Detox Maven repo in `android/build.gradle`; `testBuildType` + `testInstrumentationRunner` + `androidTestImplementation('com.wix:detox:+')` in `android/app/build.gradle`; manifest references `network_security_config` (cleartext to Metro `10.0.2.2`).
- **iOS:** `cd ios && pod install` (generates `.xcworkspace`); scheme/workspace names match `.detoxrc.js`.
- If any piece is missing, complete setup first — see `docs/DETOX-INTEGRATION.md`.

## testIDs

- E2E specs use `by.id('testID-value')`; elements must have `testID="testID-value"`.
- testIDs come from `.cursor/logs/test-cases-{feature}.md` (section **testID / selectors (for E2E)**).
- Test Case Authoring Agent fills testIDs in test cases; Fixing Agent adds or preserves testIDs when fixing E2E failures.

## Full steps

See **`docs/DETOX-INTEGRATION.md`** for setup, agent workflow, and troubleshooting.
